Build a professional website called “To-Link”. This website aims to make the neighbors’ relationship better by helping each other and participating in events, and much more. Keep this in mind, when coding/programming, you need to make sure the whole coding is easy to maintain, so when making changes/edits for the functions, the other functions will not be affected unless they have a relationship and need changes that are unavoidable. Use real API configuration and databases, do not use browser’s local storage unless unavoidable.

The To-Link website needs to have the following main pages: Login page, Register page, Home page, Quest page, Sharing page, 2nd Hand page, Lost&Find page, Nearby Shops page, Nearby Communities page, Messages page, Friends page, Clubhouse&Facilities page, AI Chat page, Documents page, Booking Status page, Calendar page, Website Setting page, Profile Setting page.

Whole website style: The website adopts a high-end, modern, clean, and high-quality professional UI design style. The overall visual style is simple, refined, youthful, and sophisticated, aligning with the positioning of a community and lifestyle service platform. The interface utilizes soft gradient colors, standardized white space, consistent rounded corner parameters, and smooth floating animations to create a refined, high-end, and professional user experience.

Login page: It will look like Facebook, the screen split into 2 parts, the left is a logo/slogan/title part, and the right is a login form. The login form requires inputting registered email address/phone/username, then password. Above the login button there is a Remember Me check box that will save the login data for future login. Under the login button will show a “Forgot/Change Password” button and under it will have a “Register New Account” button. When pressed the “Forgot/Change Password” button, the login form will switch to a form that asks users to input the email address they registered the account, then an email will send to that email address. The email is a link; by clicking the link, it will send the user to a page that asks the user to enter their email address and new password for the To-Link account. After submitting the email and new password, user can now use the new password to login. When user pressed the “Register New Account” button will switch the login form into a register form, then user need to fill in their First Name, Last Name, email address, phone number, HKID/Personal ID, country, current state(drop down: worker/employee/jobless/student), job title(only show when the user chooses worker or employee). After filling in the information, the register form will switch back to a login form, users need to fill in the login information to continue.

Whole website layout: The whole website is not scrollable, only items inside containers are scrollable, like words, posts, and quests, etc. I will tell you the percentages of each item so each item is small enough to fit in the screen and users no need to scroll on the website, so they can scroll inside of the containers. Top bar's width is 8% of the screen, and its length is 100% of the screen. Top bar on the left side has “Menu button” & “To-Link title” ; right side has “Notification bell” & “User icon.” The “Menu button” shows/hides a side bar that use to navigate different main pages.

