Home page: There will be a “weather card” that shows the current users’ location, time, date, today's and future's weather with real data, not fake/mockup data. The weather card is only 30% of the screen size but its width is 16% of the screen, another 60% is an advertisement but its width is 16% of the screen, the rest of the 10% are the gaps that make the website look less compact. Then, for each 6 seconds, the advertisements will go to the next advertisement, if it reaches the last one, it will loop back to the first one. The advertisement will have “<“ button on the left side of the advertisement to let user see the previous advertisement and “>“ button on the right side of the advertisement to let user see the next advertisement and “  .  .  .  “ navigate button on the bottom of the advertisement to let users know how many advertisement there are and let them choose which advertisement they want to see, the number of “  .  “ will change based on how many advertisement there are, if there are only 1 advertisement, there will only have 1 “dot”, if there have 2 advertisements, there will have 2 “dots” and so on, only admin can edit the advertisements. Under the weather card and advertisement, there is a “container” its length is 90% of the screen size, the rest of the 10% is the gap that makes the website look less compact, and its width is 16% of the screen, it will show the admin's message, only admin account can edit the message. Under the “admin's message” container, there will be 3 columns, 30% of the screen size for each column and its height is 50%, the rest of the 10% of the width and length are the gaps for each column and the gaps for the screen to look less compact. The first column is called “Recent Sharing,” this column will show at most 5 newest posts(sharing) of the current login user's post(sharing), when user scroll to the bottom, there is a “View More” button that leads the user to the main function page -> “Sharing page”. Each post(sharing) will have title, 2 lines of description, if the description is too long, it will show “...” at the end, there will also have “Like button” on the bottom left corner, “Comment button” on the right of the like button, “Edit button” on the left side of the delete button and “Delete button” on the bottom right corner. The post(sharing) itself is clickable, it will show a pop-up window that shows the whole post(sharing) content. The like button will have a number that tells how many likes this post(sharing) has, the total likes are also including yourself liking it, each user is only allowed to like once for each post(sharing). The comment button will have a number that tells how many comments this post(sharing) has, after clicking it, it will pop up a window that shows the other users’ comments and it lets you comment on it too, each user is allowed to comment unlimitedly. The edit button when clicked will show a pop-up window that lets you edit anything in that post(sharing), including title, description, tags, images, videos. After saving the edited post(sharing), the post(sharing) will have a light grey “edited” word on the top right corner of that post(sharing). The delete button when click will show a pop-up confirmation window that asks user, “Are you sure you want to delete this post?.” There is red “Delete” and light grey “No” button, the “Delete” button are on the bottom left corner, and “No” button is on the bottom right corner. The “Delete” button will show a count down like this “Delete (3)” -> “Delete (2)” -> “Delete (1)” -> “Delete”. The button is not clickable, and its color is dark red, when the countdown is finish, the button will turn to red and clickable, and when click, the post(sharing) will be deleted, and the deleted posts(sharing) will move to “History” storage located inside “Profile Settings.” The “No” button is light grey color with no countdown, user can click it anytime without waiting. The second column is “Your Quests,” this column will show all the “quests” you posted and the quests are waiting other users to accept. Each “Your Quests” quests will have title, 2 lines of description, if the description is too long, it will show “...” at the end, there will also have “Edit button” on the left side of the delete button and “Delete button” on the bottom right corner. The quest itself is clickable, it will show a pop-up window that shows the whole quest content. The edit button when clicked will show a pop-up window that lets you edit anything in that quest, including title, description, tags, images, videos. After saving the edited quest, the quest will have a light grey “edited” word on the top right corner of that quest. The delete button works exactly the same as the post's delete button but the confirmation message is “Are you sure you want to delete this quest?.” The third column is called “Accepted Quest,” this column will show all the “quests” other users posted and you accepted it (to remind you complete the quest you accepted). Each “Accepted Quest” quests will have title, 2 lines of description, if the description is too long, it will show “...” at the end, there will also have “Contact Requester button” on the bottom right corner. The quest itself is clickable, it will show a pop-up window that shows the whole quest content. The contact requester button when clicked will make you go to the main function page “Messages page” and automatically opens the chat room of the requester.

Posts page: There are 4 tabs for sub-pages: Quest page, Sharing page, 2nd Hand page, Lost&Find page.

Posts page(Quest page): There will be a search bar to search for words that exist in the quest including title, description, tags, time. On the right side of the search bar there is a “sort drop down” that can let user choose: Highest Reward, Time Limited(quest with not much time left will show first), Latest, Least Reward, Oldest. On the right side of the “sort drop down”, there is a “Show/Hide Your Quests” switch, when the switch is On(Hide), it will only show the other users’ quests and hide your quests, then if the switch is Off(Show), it will only show your created quests. On the very right side of it, there is a “Create Quest” button for user to create their own quest. After clicking it, it will show a pop-up window that lets users input the following things: title, description, tags, time range(the time when the quest itself will disappear automatically when times up), at most 5 images and at most 3 videos. The time range section will look like this:
[No Time Limt]
[Today] [“day”:“month”] to [“day”:“month”]
[Now] [“hour”:“minute”] to [“hour”:“minute”]
Users have to either choose [No Time Limit] or select the time range day, month, hour and minute.
The [No Time Limit] is a button, by clicking the [No Time Limit] button, users no need to choose the time range, and the post will not automatically disappear.
The [Today] is a button, by clicking the [Today] button both left and right [ : ] will automatically enter the day and month they currently click the button, if they didn’t click the [Today] button or they want to change the date, they can enter their desire date by click the [ : ] and a small calendar will show to let user choose the date. The [Now] is a button, by clicking the [Now] button the left [ : ] will automatically enter the hour and minute they currently click the button but the right [ : ] are still remain empty and needed to fill in, if they didn’t click the [Now] button, they can enter their desire time by click the [ : ] and a small clock will show to let user choose the time. When user type “buy items + Enter on keyboard” in tag section, it will “save” and the tag will show as “#buy items”, and the type bar will clear and let user type the next tag if they want. Users are allowed to only add at most 10 tags. After user submits the form, the pop-up will close and sends users back to the “Quest page”. In the quest page, the quest itself is clickable and when click, will show a pop-up that show the whole quest’s detail. The screen size will determine how many quests will show in one row and the quest size(width and length) are fixed, if the screen is big enough to fit 4 quests in one row, it will show 4 quests in one row, but if the screen is too small, it will show 3 instead, and so on. Each quest will have “. . .” on the top right corner, when click, will show a drop down: Report User, Block User. When click report user, it will show a pop-up that asks user to choose the report type, for example: Spam, Inappropriate contents, etc, there is also an option “Others” when choose, will show a type box to let user type the reason, there are 2 buttons in the bottom right corner that acts as submit: Report, Report&Block. When click Report, the report will send to admin’s account and show a role=“alert” message telling users the report is sent to admin and will be review, thank you. When click Report&Block, the report will send to admin’s account and show a role=“alert” message telling users the report is sent to admin and will be review, thank you, and the report user will not see the reported user again, unless they unblock them in the setting menu’s “Block List”. On the bottom right corner, there is a “Accept Quest” button, when click will show a pop-up that ask user to enter “why they think they are capable of doing this job”, when submit, will send the user to the requester chat room and will send a special message that looks different from normal chat message bubble, this special message is clickable and will show the quest’s title, description, accept time, and the reason of “why they think they are capable of doing this job”, if the poster think this person is not capable of doing this job, they can click the “Deny” button inside the special message bubble and optionally let the poster enter why deny the accepter, the declined users are not allowed to accept the same quest immediately, they need to wait 30 minutes to re-accept the same quest. But, if the poster thinks this person is capable of doing this job, they can click the “Accept” button inside the special message bubble, then only this person can do the quest, other applied users will automatically decline and send a “This quest is already accepted by others” message to notify the declined users, and the accepted post is not acceptable for other users. When the quest is finished, both users needed to click the “Finish(0/2)” button under the special bubble, either user click the finish button, the number will go up -> “Finish(1/2)”, if both users clicked it and make the number to (2/2), the quest will be counted as finished, and the user who accept the quest and complete the quest will receive reward points, and a “We appreciate your efforts.” message. On the left side of “Accept Quest” button will have a “Contact Requester button” that acts exactly the same as the one in the “Your Quests” in the home page.

Posts page(Sharing page): The search bar and Show/Hide switch function are same as the Quest page, but it now only affects Sharing page. The sort drop down in this page is now show: Time Limited(post with not much time left will show first), Latest, Oldest. There is also a “Create Sharing Post” button, the form acts the same as the quest’s form, but the words inside it may different. Each Sharing posts will have “. . .” on the top right corner, when click, will show a drop down: Report User, Block User. These 2 button functions are exactly the same as the one on the Quest page. Each sharing post there is a “Like” and “Comment” button on the bottom left corner. When click “Like”, the empty heart icon will fill with red color and the number next to it will go up, each user can only like each post once. The “Comment” button when click will expand the whole post and show other users comment on the side of it, and it also let the current user leave a comment on it.

Posts page(2nd Hand page): The search bar and Show/Hide switch function are same as the Quest page and Sharing page, but it now only affects 2nd Hand page. The sort drop down in this page is now show: Cheapest, Time Limited(post with not much time left will show first), Latest, Most Expensive, Oldest. There is also a “Create 2nd Hand Post” button, the form acts the same as the quest’s form, but the words inside it may different. The form will have a “Price” for user to type, there is a “$” on the left side of the type bar, if the item is free, they need to type “0” in the bar. Each 2nd Hand posts will have “. . .” on the top right corner, when click, will show a drop down: Report User, Block User. These 2 button functions are exactly the same as the one on the Quest page. There is a “Trade” or “Get” button on the bottom right corner of each 2nd hand post, to determine is trade or get, is determined by the 2nd hand items are free or need money. When they click the button, it will automatically send a message using the special message bubble saying “Hey, I’m interested in this item.”, then show the item’s details below the special message bubble.

Posts page(Lost&Find page) The search bar and Show/Hide switch function are same as the Quest page and Sharing page and 2nd Hand page, but it now only affects Lost&Find page. The sort drop down in this page is now show: Highest Reward, Time Limited(quest with not much time left will show first), Latest, Least Reward, Oldest. There is also a “Create Lost&Find Post” button, the form acts the same as the 2nd hands’ form, but the words inside it may different. The form will have a “Price” for user to type just like the 2nd hand form. Each Lost&Find posts will have “. . .” on the top right corner, when click, will show a drop down: Report User, Block User. These 2 button functions are exactly the same as the one on the Quest page and 2nd hand page. There is a “Contact Owner” and “Clues” and “Found It !” button on the bottom right corner of each L&F post, when click the “Contact Owner” the user will send to the poster’s/owner’s message chat room. If user click “Clues”, user will need to enter where and when they have seen the item/pet/child and optionally upload at most 3 photos. After sending it, the special message bubble will show the place and time the “clue giver” entered. If the user who create the L&F post find this “clue” useful, they can click “Helpful” button under the special bubble, then the “clue finder” will receive a small amount of reward point. If they found it not useful, they can click the “Not Helpful” button, when they click it, a pop-up will show asking “Do you want to report this message?”, there are 3 buttons, “No”, “Report”, “Report and Block”. When click “No”, the pop-up will close and do nothing. When click “Report”, will show another pop-up and ask what type of trash message that is, like: spam, inappropriate, etc. When click “Report and Block”, will show another pop-up just like the previous one, then it will ask user the trash type, and after submitting, it will block the reported user, when block, they can’t see and receive their posts, messages, any other things as well.

