Connections page(Messages page): This Messages page will look like Instagram and WhatsApp, the left side are the chat rooms/users, the right side are the messages. On the left side of the chat rooms, above those chat rooms, there is a search bar to search the chat room/user names, next to the search bar there is a “Create Group Chat” button, when click, it will show a pop-up window, users need to choose who to add to the group chat, they can type the username and there will be suggestion users appear under the type field, or they can click the friended users to add them in the group chat. Users are only able to create group chat if they add at least 3 people including the current user.

Connections page(Friends page): This Friends page will have 2 main parts; the first part is the suggestion&search section. When the user is on this page, the suggestion&search section will show some other users “user card” in the section. There will be a search bar for users to search the usernames. When users type anything in the search bar, the suggestion users will clear and show the searching user, for example, when I type “Bo” the section should show users’ “user card” that include “bo” in their username, like “bobby”, “lobster”, “bobo”, “modboom”. When the user clears the search bar the suggestion section will show the suggestion friends “user card” again. Under the suggestion&search section, there will be a “Friend List” that shows the friended users, each friended user will show their “online status”, profile picture, name, bio, and “Message” button and “Unfriend” button. When click message button will send the user to their chat room, if they haven’t message before, it will open a new chat room. If they have message each other before, it will open their chat room with previous messages. When click unfriend button, it will show a pop-up that ask, “Are you sure you want to unfriend this person?” with a “Yes” and “No” button. When select “Yes” the user will be removed from the friend list. If user choose “No”, the pop-up will close and nothing happen. The “online status” is a small circle on the bottom right of the profile picture with 3 available colors, green, grey, red. If the user is logged in and using the website, the circle will show green(Online). If the user is logged out or they are not using the website, the circle will show grey(Offline). If the user chooses their status as “Busy” inside profile setting, the circle will show red(Busy), no matter the user is online or offline, the red circle will not change.

Activities page(Booking Status page): This page will show the booking status for all the bookings including restaurants, any places, club house, etc, bookings. The booking status will have 4 statutes: Pending, Accept, Deny, Canceled. When user send a booking form/request to that place, the booking status is grey style “Pending”, when the place owner confirm the booking is legit and available. On the owner side, they will see an incoming booking request with 4 buttons: “Accept”, “Deny”, “Message”, “…” . On the bottom right corner will have a green style “Accept” button, when click, the booking details will show again, under the details, will ask owner, “Are you sure you confirm this booking?”. On the little bit of the left side of the “Accept” button, is a red style “Deny” button, when click, the owner needs to provide a reason why deny the booking. On the little bit of the left side of the “Deny” button, there is a “Message” button, when click, will send the owner to the booking requester chat room. On the top right corner, there is a “…” button, when click will show “Report” and “Report&Block”, the function of these 2 buttons is explained before. After owner confirm the booking by clicking the confirmation button, then the user will see the booking status change to a green style “Accept”. If the place owner denies the booking request, the owner needs to provide a reason to deny the booking and the user side will see their booking status will change to a red style “Deny” status. Both user and owner can use a “Message” button to directly find the people who tries to book the place, so they can ask more details/information directly. On the booking requester side, they will see 2 buttons, bottom right corner is a “Message” button, when click will send the user to the owner’s chat room. Left bottom corner is a “Cancel Booking” button, when pressed will ask the user “Are you sure you want to cancel this booking?” with a “Yes”, “No” button, when choose “Yes”, the booking 